item.title: CVE-2022-3676|2024-08-03T01:14:03.367Z -- the%20eclipse%20foundation -- eclipse%20openj9
item.description: In Eclipse Openj9 before version 0.35.0, interface calls can be inlined without a runtime type check. Malicious bytecode could make use of this inlining to access or modify memory via an incompatible type.
